Internal architecture and extension points for the [[Table-of-Contents Macros]].

!! State Tiddlers and $qualify

The expandable toc macros use `$qualify` to create unique state tiddler paths. The path is built from:

> `$:/state/toc` + <<.param path>> + `-` + <<.var currentTiddler>>

The <<.param path>> accumulates as the tree recurses: each level appends `/` and the current tag. This ensures that the same tiddler appearing in different branches of the tree has independent open/close state.

When embedding multiple TOCs in the same tiddler, `$qualify` further ensures unique state by incorporating the tiddler's position in the widget tree.

!! Programmatic Branch Control

<<.from-version "5.4.0">>

The `toc-openBranch` and `toc-closeBranch` procedures accept a `manual` parameter (default: `"no"`). When set to `"yes"`, the branch opens or closes without requiring a CTRL-click:

|Procedure |`manual:"yes"` |CTRL-click |h
|`toc-openBranch` |Opens the branch and recursively opens all children |Same behaviour |
|`toc-closeBranch` |Closes the branch and deletes all child state tiddlers |Same behaviour |

This is useful for plugin authors who want to programmatically expand or collapse specific branches.

See [[Examples/TOC/advanced/open-close-branch-buttons]] for a working example.

!! Deprecated: itemClassFilter Parameter

The `itemClassFilter` parameter still appears in all macro signatures for backwards compatibility but is no longer used. It has been replaced by the internal [[$:/core/macros/toc]] `tf.toc-itemClassFilter` function, which automatically handles the `toc-item-selected` class in tabbed mode.

Existing code that passes `itemClassFilter` will not break, but the parameter is silently ignored.

