The simple <<.var toc>> macro is the exception â€” it does ''not'' reuse the expandable macros. This makes it a useful reference implementation for debugging, as it is self-contained in `toc` and `toc-body`.

Key internal functions and procedures:

|Name |Type |Purpose |h
|`tf.toc-filterString` |function |Returns the correct filter string based on mode (tag/parentField/tagField) |
|`tf.toc-mode` |function |Returns the current mode: `tagMode`, `tocpMode`, or `tagLikeMode` |
|`tf.toc-hasChildren` |function |Returns a filter string to check if a node has children (mode-aware) |
|`tf.toc-hide` |function |Evaluates the `toc-hide` field: returns a titlelist for `yes`, or the field content as filter |
|`tf.toc-include` |function |Reads the `toc-include` field from the current tag/parent |
|`tf.toc-filter` |function |Reads the `toc-filter` field from the current tag/parent |
|`tf.toc-itemClass` |function |Joins all CSS classes for a node (selected, include, filter, hide) |
|`tf.toc-getItemTemplateTitle` |function |Resolves template: tiddler field takes precedence over macro parameter |
|`tf.toc-getTooltip` |function |Returns tooltip text: `toc-tooltip` field or fallback to title |
|`tf.toc-stateTitle` |function |Builds the state tiddler path for open/close state |
|`tf.toc-stateIsClosed` |function |Checks if a branch is in closed state |
|`tf.toc-stateIsOpen` |function |Checks if a branch is open (or `tv-toc-expand` is yes) |